fielddes: Unique ID of an Executive.
Unique ID of an Organization. An Organization is the concept of a company, which is constructed as a collection of Legal Entities (child and parent entities) and Locations (e.g., offices, stores).

Primary name of the Organization, derived from multiple sources including the IRS, Dept. of Labor, SEC, SBA, and local jurisdictions. A waterfall is in place to pick the Organization's primary name, with preference given to IRS related sources.
TICKER of the Organization if it is publicly listed.

Link to the Organization's primary website. A company's website is not usually included in the regulatory filings, but BQ uses alternative methods to identify these links, which may result in occasional inaccuracies.
Full name of the Executive.
First name of the Executive.
Middle name's Initial of the Executive.
Middle name of the Executive.
Last name of the Executive.
List of all Titles held by the Executive within the Organization. There are 32 distinct Titles for Executives.
Highest Title held by the Executive.

Link to the Executive's primary LinkedIn URL. The LinkedIn URL is not reported in regulatory filings; therefore, BQ scrapes the Internet to find such links, and consequently the process is subject to error.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Executive has signatory authority, and 0 otherwise. This is attributable from filings with the corresponding legal entity's jurisdiction.
Mobile phone number directly associated with the Executive.
Landline phone number directly associated with the Executive.
Mobile number directly associated with the Executive formatted per the US Standards.
Landline phone number directly associated with the Executive formatted per the US standards.
Mobile phone number indirectly associated with the Executive.
Landline phone number indirectly associated with the Executive.
Mobile number indirectly associated with the Executive formatted per the US Standards.
Landline phone number indirectly associated with the Executive formatted per the US standards.
All Emails of the Executive.
All previously known email IDs of the Executive.
Personal email IDs of the Executive.
Current work email IDs of the Executive.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Executive address is directly associated with that Executive.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Executive address is valid based on a match with the USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
1st line of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
2nd line of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
City of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State abbreviation of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State name of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County-level FIPS code of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County name of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Country of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
5-digit zip code of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
9-digit zip code (ZIP + 4) of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Zip code classification of the Executive's address stating whether it is a P.O. Box or not. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Numerical portion (if any) of the 2nd line of the Executive's address, such as a unit or suite number. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Executive's address is the "default" address for a building ( i.e., the main lobby) and 0 otherwise. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Latitude of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Longitude of the Executive's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Classification that indicates whether the Executive's address is Match-Mailable or Non-Mailable based on USPS reporting.
RDI indicates whether the Executive's address is Residential, Commercial, P.O. Box or Unknown based on USPS reporting.
Indicator that states "Yes" if the Executive's address is verified to be deliverable based on the Delivery Point Validation Process of USPS.
Name of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Executive's address lies according to USPS.

The Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) is a 5-digit numeric code which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Executive's address lies according to USPS.
Metro or Micro Type classification of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) in which the Executive's address lies according to USPS.
Congressional District Code of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
All Phones of the Executive.
All  formated Phones of the Executive.
